11#include "common_video/include/incoming_video_stream.h"

16#include "absl/types/optional.h"

18#include "rtc_base/checks.h"
19#include "rtc_base/trace_event.h"

21namespace webrtc {
22
23IncomingVideoStream::IncomingVideoStream(
24 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
25 int32_t delay_ms,
26 rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>* callback)
27 : render_buffers_(delay_ms),
28 callback_(callback),
29 incoming_render_queue_(task_queue_factory->CreateTaskQueue(
30 "IncomingVideoStream",
31 TaskQueueFactory::Priority::HIGH)) {}
32
33IncomingVideoStream::~IncomingVideoStream() {
34 RTC_DCHECK(main_thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
35}
36
37void IncomingVideoStream::OnFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame) {
38 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "IncomingVideoStream::OnFrame");
39 RTC_CHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&decoder_race_checker_);
40 RTC_DCHECK(!incoming_render_queue_.IsCurrent());
41 // TODO(srte): Using video_frame = std::move(video_frame) would move the frame
42 // into the lambda instead of copying it, but it doesn't work unless we change
43 // OnFrame to take its frame argument by value instead of const reference.
44 incoming_render_queue_.PostTask([this, video_frame = video_frame]() mutable {
45 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&incoming_render_queue_);
46 if (render_buffers_.AddFrame(std::move(video_frame)) == 1)
47 Dequeue();
48 });
49}
50
51void IncomingVideoStream::Dequeue() {
52 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "IncomingVideoStream::Dequeue");
53 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&incoming_render_queue_);
54 absl::optional<VideoFrame> frame_to_render = render_buffers_.FrameToRender();
55 if (frame_to_render)
56 callback_->OnFrame(*frame_to_render);
57
58 if (render_buffers_.HasPendingFrames()) {
59 uint32_t wait_time = render_buffers_.TimeToNextFrameRelease();
60 incoming_render_queue_.PostDelayedTask([this]() { Dequeue(); }, wait_time);
61 }
62}
63
64} // namespace webrtc
